Sahara Heads for Biggest Drop Since May on Unit Output Halt

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-07-17T09:05:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/sahara-heads-for-biggest-drop-since-may-on-unit-output-halt.html
Sahara Petrochemical Co. (SPC)  headed for
the biggest drop in more than two months after the manufacturer
of chemicals said the polypropylene plant of its unit Al Waha
Petrochemicals stopped production due to a technical fault.  The shares dropped 3.1 percent, poised for the biggest
decline since May 7, to 25.30 riyals at 11:57 a.m. in Riyadh.
